<item>
            <title>[CXF-2711] Concurrency issue with AsyncHandler</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-2711</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The problem is on the access to the ClientCallback.done boolean&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can have a situation where the client uses the Future object he got from the dispatch.invokeAsync() method.&lt;br/&gt;
It performs an active wait using Future.isDone()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On another Thread, the WS response comes back, and the JaxwsClientCallback.handlerResponse() is called. The handler provided by the client is called, so far everything went well. After the AsyncHandler.handleResponse() invocation, the ClientCallback set the &apos;done&apos; boolean to true.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But this value change is never seen by the Future.isDone() invocations!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Because the ClientCallback.done boolean is not &apos;volatile&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve made a try with a volatile &apos;done&apos; and it works perfectly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could it be possible that this simple change makes it to the 2.2.7 ?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;OW2 JOnAS 5.2&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
